      <description>I applaud the concept of community documentation - for years, comments have been added to the online documentation providing information not within the docs; and community members are more likely to provide documentation, as an easy way to give back to the community (see forums).&#13;
&#13;
However, I don't think forums + SVN /docs are the best way to contribute.  I think a wiki + discussions would serve the online community better, and could inform the official documentation.&#13;
&#13;
Your thoughts?</description>
